Scale Up

Diagram
User -> DNS -> HAproxy 1 + HAproxy 2 (cluster) -> Web Server -> Application Server -> Database Server

What is added
- One additional server: splits the infrastructure into separate tiers so each component has dedicated resources.
- HAproxy configured as a cluster: removes the load balancer as a bottleneck and improves availability.
- Split services: web server, application server, and database are placed on their own servers.

Why these elements are added
- Separate web server: handles HTTP requests efficiently.
- Separate application server: runs application logic without competing with web or database workloads.
- Separate database server: isolates data storage and improves performance and maintenance.
- Load balancer cluster: distributes traffic and reduces single points of failure.

Benefit
- This design scales better because each layer can be scaled independently based on demand.
